WEBVTT

00:00.421 --> 00:02.833
♪♪

00:04.505 --> 00:08.089
Lewie, Beast and Daphne
are away for the weekend,

00:08.089 --> 00:09.720
which means I get to
do something

00:09.720 --> 00:11.552
I've never done before.

00:13.804 --> 00:15.766
The backwards couch flop.

00:15.766 --> 00:18.099
Normally, if I did this,

00:18.099 --> 00:19.940
I would land on
at least four other people,

00:19.940 --> 00:21.482
and half a pizza.

00:22.903 --> 00:25.066
This is what it's like
 not sharing a bathroom.

00:25.066 --> 00:26.907
I actually have time
 to brush all my teeth,

00:26.907 --> 00:28.949
not just the ones
 that show.

00:28.949 --> 00:31.112
And this, my friends,
 is what it's like

00:31.112 --> 00:32.743
to not have to
 kidney punch people

00:32.743 --> 00:35.116
to get to the milk.

00:35.116 --> 00:37.748
Even if it smells like cheese
that's been left in a gym bag.

00:40.791 --> 00:42.423
Listen up.

00:42.423 --> 00:46.217
With your mom and the tornado
trio at Grandma's

00:46.217 --> 00:48.259
tonight may be the first time
in 16 years

00:48.259 --> 00:50.971
that I've been able to watch
an entire ball game.

00:50.971 --> 00:53.474
So unless there's a fire,
a felony or a fracture,

00:53.474 --> 00:54.885
forget I'm your father.

00:54.885 --> 00:56.677
Already forgotten.
Got plans.

00:56.677 --> 00:58.099
- Me, too.
- Me, too too.

00:58.099 --> 00:59.850
Wait.

00:59.850 --> 01:02.443
Does that mean I'll be the only
kid in the house tonight?

01:02.443 --> 01:04.144
That's like Halley's Comet.

01:04.144 --> 01:07.027
It only happens
every 75 years.

01:07.027 --> 01:08.949
Like Beast putting
the toilet seat up.

01:08.949 --> 01:11.612
Or down.
Or even hitting the toilet.

01:11.612 --> 01:15.286
Look, I love
my brothers and sisters,

01:15.286 --> 01:16.827
but because of them,

01:16.827 --> 01:19.870
I've never had
a successful slumber party.

01:19.870 --> 01:23.334
My friends either get driven
away by the younger kids...

01:23.334 --> 01:26.167
HARLEY: Beast, Lewie, no!

01:27.208 --> 01:30.010
Or sucked in
by the older ones.

01:30.010 --> 01:32.633
Changing your part
adds instant bounce.

01:32.633 --> 01:36.307
Body, blah.

01:36.307 --> 01:39.640
Body, blah.

01:39.640 --> 01:41.272
GIRLS: Oh!

01:41.272 --> 01:45.025
But tonight, all that's
going to change.

01:45.025 --> 01:48.189
Dad, can I have
a slumber party?

01:48.189 --> 01:50.281
That sounds like a question
for your father.

01:50.281 --> 01:51.652
I'm just some guy
watching the game.

01:51.652 --> 01:53.944
Well, if you see my dad,

01:53.944 --> 01:55.156
tell him thanks.

02:01.452 --> 02:04.505
What's this?
Flavored creamer?

02:06.917 --> 02:09.008
Nice. Cheesecake.

02:10.920 --> 02:13.254
Nothing but the best
for you, Dad.

02:13.254 --> 02:14.885
♪ Hey, hey, hey ♪

02:17.678 --> 02:21.852
♪ Sometimes it feels like
things are outta control ♪

02:21.852 --> 02:25.436
♪ Like you're living in
a circus ♪

02:25.436 --> 02:28.899
♪ Tryin' to figure out
your way in the world ♪

02:28.899 --> 02:32.072
♪ Where you're at
is kinda perfect ♪

02:32.072 --> 02:34.074
♪ So turn it up,
turn it up ♪

02:34.074 --> 02:35.986
♪ Do your thing,
don't stop ♪

02:35.986 --> 02:39.079
♪ Let the games begin,
let's jump right in ♪

02:39.079 --> 02:42.373
♪ I wanna get
stuck with you ♪

02:42.373 --> 02:44.545
♪ In the middle
of the party ♪

02:44.545 --> 02:46.547
♪ We're just
getting started ♪

02:46.547 --> 02:49.880
♪ I wanna get
stuck with you ♪

02:49.880 --> 02:53.554
♪ In the eye of the tornado,
rowin' in the same boat ♪

02:53.554 --> 02:56.677
♪ I wanna get
stuck with you ♪

02:56.677 --> 03:00.891
♪ Get stuck in
the middle with you ♪

03:00.891 --> 03:03.063
♪ I wanna get
stuck with you ♪

03:07.017 --> 03:08.479
All of the stars
have aligned for

03:08.479 --> 03:10.731
Harley's Comet Sleepover,

03:10.731 --> 03:13.574
which includes an actual comet
we're gonna watch from the roof.

03:13.574 --> 03:15.576
Sure, the roof's off limits,

03:15.576 --> 03:18.118
but the tattletales
have left the building.

03:18.118 --> 03:19.450
Think fast!

03:22.243 --> 03:23.664
Was that a pass to me?

03:23.664 --> 03:25.246
Not important.

03:25.246 --> 03:26.827
What is important is tonight,

03:26.827 --> 03:28.919
league MVP
and my personal hero

03:28.919 --> 03:30.921
Mikaela Mendoza
drops her new,

03:30.921 --> 03:32.423
limited edition
basketball shoe.

03:32.423 --> 03:33.924
I wrote all about it
on my blog.

03:33.924 --> 03:36.757
- "I'm a basket case."
- You nailed the title.

03:36.757 --> 03:38.839
Come on. We gotta go now
to get a good place in line.

03:38.839 --> 03:40.801
Georgie, I can't.

03:40.801 --> 03:42.763
I have plans,
once-in-a-lifetime plans.

03:42.763 --> 03:44.605
But you promised
you'd go with me.

03:44.605 --> 03:46.267
I did? When?

03:47.938 --> 03:49.900
Since I'm helping you test
your new spray tanning helmet,

03:49.900 --> 03:51.402
will you come with me

03:51.402 --> 03:52.983
to get new basketball shoes
next weekend?

03:52.983 --> 03:55.486
Sorry, Georgie.
I'm pretty busy.

03:57.908 --> 03:59.280
How's my tan?

03:59.280 --> 04:00.571
Amazing, right?

04:00.571 --> 04:01.782
Grab me a mirror.

04:01.782 --> 04:03.784
Forget the mirror.

04:03.784 --> 04:05.576
Tell me all about
these super cool

04:05.576 --> 04:07.918
- basketball shoes
we're getting.
- Okay.

04:07.918 --> 04:10.331
Right.
The Oompa Loompa incident.

04:10.331 --> 04:12.212
Just because
I love basketball

04:12.212 --> 04:13.714
doesn't mean
I wanna look like one.

04:13.714 --> 04:15.586
Can't you just go alone?

04:15.586 --> 04:18.969
No. They only give out
one pair per person,
and I need two--

04:18.969 --> 04:21.512
one to play in
and one to look perfect
when I walk down the aisle.

04:21.512 --> 04:23.804
I'm sure I'll read
all about it on your blog.

04:23.804 --> 04:25.386
We're jetting in 20.

04:25.386 --> 04:27.808
We'll be in line all night,
so don't wear tight shoes.

04:27.808 --> 04:31.231
You don't wanna end up
with feet like basketball
legend Andrea Ahlgreen.

04:31.231 --> 04:32.813
Hammer toes.

04:39.490 --> 04:41.742
Later.

04:41.742 --> 04:43.994
Yeah, okay.

04:43.994 --> 04:46.407
Whoa!
Where do you think
you're going?

04:46.407 --> 04:49.580
Library. Hannah's picking
me up to do homework.

04:49.580 --> 04:51.792
- ( motorcycle revs )
- Bye.

04:51.792 --> 04:54.505
I know that sound.
That's the sound of you
dropping out of school.

04:54.505 --> 04:56.877
- No, it's Cuff.
- One leads to the other.

04:56.877 --> 04:59.009
I don't know
what bothers me more,

04:59.009 --> 05:00.881
that you lied to me,
or you put so little
effort into it.

05:00.881 --> 05:03.344
Really? I put so little
effort into everything,

05:03.344 --> 05:04.975
except this.

05:04.975 --> 05:07.478
I didn't think
you'd care that much.
You're not Mom.

05:07.478 --> 05:09.640
Sure, you get
mad and stuff,

05:09.640 --> 05:11.982
but Mom's the one
that brings the punishment.

05:11.982 --> 05:13.894
It works for you guys.
Why mess with it?

05:16.697 --> 05:18.399
Come on, Ethan.

05:18.399 --> 05:20.441
You gotta go with
Georgie for me.

05:20.441 --> 05:23.073
I've got one night to go
through Beast and Lewie's stuff

05:23.073 --> 05:25.536
and get my stuff back.
No dice.

05:25.536 --> 05:28.619
Actually, dice.

05:28.619 --> 05:30.541
What's more important,

05:30.541 --> 05:33.714
your stuff
or your favorite sister?

05:33.714 --> 05:35.045
My favorite video game,

05:35.045 --> 05:36.717
my favorite comic book,

05:36.717 --> 05:39.800
algebra book.
This can stay lost.

05:39.800 --> 05:41.632
I wonder if those
little looters

05:41.632 --> 05:43.464
have my snow jacket.

05:43.464 --> 05:44.885
I'm going back in.

05:44.885 --> 05:46.557
Raiders of the Lost Parka.

05:49.730 --> 05:52.893
I'm trying to do you
a solid here, bro.

05:52.893 --> 05:56.437
All my girls are coming
over for a sleepover tonight,

05:56.437 --> 05:58.479
and I know how much
you enjoy that.

